<title>Key Concepts</title>
<list bullet-style="bulleted" id="list-00018">
<item>There are several common measures of voting fairness, including the majority criterion, the head-to head criterion, the monotonicity criterion, and the irrelevant alternatives criterion.</item>
<item>According to Arrow’s Impossibility Theorem, each voting method in which the only information is theorder of preference of the voters will violate one of these fairness criteria.</item>
